      "title": "Handling Conflicts",
      "file": "package.json",
      "line": 1,
      "description": "## Merge Conflicts\n\nSometimes two people change the same code. This creates a **conflict**.\n\n### What a conflict looks like:\n```\n<<<<<<< HEAD\nconst color = 'blue';\n=======\nconst color = 'red';\n>>>>>>> feature/change-color\n```\n\n### How to fix:\n\n1. **Decide** which version to keep (or combine both)\n2. **Remove** the conflict markers (`<<<<`, `====`, `>>>>`)\n3. **Save** the file\n4. **Commit** the resolved file\n\n### Fixed version:\n```\nconst color = 'blue';  // Or 'red', or whatever is correct\n```\n\n### Tips to avoid conflicts:\n- Pull from main often\n- Keep branches short-lived\n- Communicate with team about who's working on what"
