      "title": "üìã To Do: Contribute Your First Feature",
      "file": "package.json",
      "line": 1,
      "description": "## üìã To Do: Contribute Your First Feature\n\nLet's practice the complete Git workflow by adding a small feature.\n\n---\n\n### Step 1: Update Main Branch\n```bash\ngit checkout main\ngit pull origin main\n```\n\n### Step 2: Create Feature Branch\n```bash\ngit checkout -b feature/add-loading-spinner\n```\n\n### Step 3: Make Changes\nAdd a loading spinner component or improve an existing feature.\n\n### Step 4: Stage and Commit\n```bash\n# Check what changed\ngit status\ngit diff\n\n# Stage changes\ngit add src/components/atoms/Spinner/\n\n# Commit with proper message\ngit commit -m \"feat: add reusable loading spinner component\n\n- Created Spinner atom with size variants\n- Added animation using TailwindCSS\n- Exported from atoms index\"\n```\n\n### Step 5: Push to GitHub\n```bash\ngit push -u origin feature/add-loading-spinner\n```\n\n### Step 6: Create Pull Request\n1. Go to GitHub repository\n2. Click \"Compare & pull request\"\n3. Fill in description:\n```markdown\n## Summary\nAdded a reusable loading spinner component.\n\n## Changes\n- Created Spinner.tsx with xs/sm/md/lg sizes\n- Uses DaisyUI loading component\n- Added SpinnerProps interface\n\n## Testing\n- [ ] Component renders in Storybook\n- [ ] All sizes work correctly\n- [ ] TypeScript has no errors\n```\n\n### Step 7: After Approval\n```bash\n# Merge on GitHub, then locally:\ngit checkout main\ngit pull origin main\ngit branch -d feature/add-loading-spinner\n```\n\n---\n\n## ‚ö†Ô∏è Watch Out For\n\n| Issue | Cause | Solution |\n|-------|-------|----------|\n| Push rejected | Remote has new commits | Run `git pull --rebase` first |\n| Merge conflicts | Same code edited | Resolve conflicts, then commit |\n| Wrong branch | Committed to main | Create branch, cherry-pick commit |\n| Forgot to pull | Stale local main | Always `git pull` before branching |\n\n---\n\n## ‚ùå Common Errors\n\n| Error Message | What It Means | How to Fix |\n|---------------|---------------|------------|\n| `Permission denied (publickey)` | SSH not configured | Add SSH key to GitHub |\n| `Updates were rejected` | Need to pull first | `git pull --rebase origin main` |\n| `Merge conflict in X` | Same lines edited | Open file, resolve `<<<<` markers |\n| `Branch 'X' not found` | Branch doesn't exist | Check branch name spelling |\n| `Nothing to commit` | No changes staged | Use `git add` first |\n\n---\n\n### ‚úÖ Checklist\n- [ ] Main branch is up to date\n- [ ] Created feature branch with good name\n- [ ] Made focused changes (one feature)\n- [ ] Committed with proper type prefix\n- [ ] Pushed to remote\n- [ ] Created PR with description\n- [ ] Addressed review feedback\n- [ ] Merged and deleted feature branch\n- [ ] Updated local main after merge"
